    "Synopsis": "The story begins when Issa receives a box on the night of his birthday from his old friend Sera. Inside the box are videotapes he left for himself 18 years earlier. In the recordings, the younger Issa explains a game called “Ezma,” which consists of a series of instructions leading to symbolic treasures designed to help him rediscover himself if he ever loses his way over time.\r\nIssa decides to follow the steps of the game with his friend Sera by his side. With every clue he solves, he is forced to confront his past and his deepest fears, while gradually reconnecting with his long-lost passion for filmmaking. Throughout this journey, Issa moves closer to fulfilling his dream of directing a documentary that creates a dialogue between his past and present, ultimately leading him to rediscover himself and understand the true meaning of love.",
